Results of Neural Network for k prediction¶

12/08/19¶

The following figures present the results of the training of the neural network for the prediction of Wear at the center. Those results are composed of three parts.

The first part, describes with text the data used for the prediction. Those data are split in eight categories, which are marked True if they have been used for prediction, False otherwise. Then are presented the results of the network over the datasets, and a specific example for a campaign. Finally, the following loading bars should not be taken into account for the results, they just correspond to Python loading the NN for following figures.

The second part shows figures of the dependency of the k parameter over the various input data. Each time, k is plotted depending on the value of one of the parameter, for each strip. Those graphs have been obtained from Dev and Test data, hence, some values can not represented in those datasets. NB: k is presented as 'with Arbitrary Unit', however, it should be homogeneous to [m/t]

The third part shows the same graphs as the second, but for the individual Wear at the center of each strip, plotted in m. In the first version of the Neural Network, the wear is computed, for a strip $[i]$, as:

$W_c[i] = k[i] * (F/w * L)[i]$

All those graphs can serve as a base for future interpretations.

Antonin Gay
